<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM2.3.5">
<l>cōttam pirāṉeṉ ṟirantāluṅ koḷḷāy</l>
<l rend="indent">curikuḻa lāroṭu nīpōyk</l>
<l>kōttuk kuravai piṇaintiṅku vantāṟ</l>
<l rend="indent">kuṇaṅkoṇ ṭiṭuvaṉō nampī</l>
<l>pērttum periyaṉa vappan taruvaṉ</l>
<l rend="indent">pirāṉē tiriyiṭa voṭṭil</l>
<l>vēyttaṭan tōḷār virumpu karuṅkuḻal</l>
<l rend="indent">viṭṭuvē nīyiṅkē vārāy</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Even though saying, ‘praise to you, O Lord!’,</l>
<l>you do not heed [my words], with curly haired women you go,</l>
<l rend="indent">clasping hands, and entwining in the kuravai,</l>
<l>if you come here, O Nampi, would I take [it as] a virtue?</l>
<l>If you acquiesce to putting the thread [in your ear], O Lord!,</l>
<l>I will give [you] big rice cakes again and again.</l>
<l>O Viṣṇu, with black curls, adored by ladies with broad, bamboo shoulders,</l>
<l>do come here!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
